title: Quake split weekend games
text:
Quake split weekend games 0 comments 
The Yellowstone Quake junior hockey team won its first game of the season, Friday night, topping the Billings Bulls, 3-2 at Riley Arena. Curtis Greenbush scored the game-winner in the third period. 
But the Quake earned only a split on the weekend by falling to the Bozeman Icedogs the next night at home, 4-3, after rallying from a 3-1 deficit. Yellowstone is now 1-3 on the season. Nick Ligocki, Nick Green and Max Doner scored in the loss to Bozeman. Subscription Required An online service is needed to view this article in its entirety.
